 @weakish: One could argue that it's a non-secure feature: your favourite site can be deleted if it's creator decide so. On IPFS even a new version of the site is not the way you like it, you can switch back to a previous one.

But yes, dynamic sites are ZeroNet's feature. And IPFS is FS. But you say that as if that's bad. ZeroNet, for example, can't deal with big files, while I used to stream videos on my ZeroNet blog page using IPFS and HTML5.

What I think, a union and collaboration is a way this things should work.

@Kaffie: how much coffee do you usually drink? You have written so much, but this time you've mostly reppeated stuff, so there wasn't point to it really xD

Webseeds are actually more secure. You can access them through tor, which is not working for DHT.

Anyway torrent is a file sharing protocol, not a secure file transfer protocol. To get something without anyone knowing it would require shut off all the good stuff from the torrent client, making it barely any better than a web downloader.
